summary: Do you think in ep 12 they set up a carnival purposefully for that episode or do you think the carnival was already set up and...
question: Do you think in ep 12 they set up a carnival purposefully for that episode or do you think the carnival was already set up and they just asked to film there?
answer: They filmed it an at a local amusement park, so they may have had to set up some props or something but most everything was already there and they had to arrange a day that they could film there. Just like with the Ferris Wheel scene with Amber and Andi, that ferris wheel is at the park where they film a lot of scenes, so they took advantage of their surroundings to use them on the show.

summary: how many people do you estimate watch on disney now? josh said that disney takes disney now views into account but im wondering...
question: how many people do you estimate watch on disney now? josh said that disney takes disney now views into account but im wondering to what extent and whether it’s any view at all that counts or just the ones in the first 24 hours/first week of an episode’s release
answer: I’m not fully sure of the details of how it works. I doubt Josh is entirely sure either tbh. TV Ratings are a system that have never really made sense to begin with and it’s never been an exact science. While traditional cable ratings are actually an estimate of viewers, Disney most likely has the ability to look at exact numbers through DisneyNOW, since they host the app internally. That’s kind of the trick of streaming services with original content now too. Most of their ratings aren’t made public, so companies like Netflix and Hulu are at an advantage when it comes to programming decisions and promoting their shows because they can base it off of social reaction more than actual ratings. But basically: Disney should be able to view their DisneyNOW ratings from any time, but I’m not sure what they pay attention to as they’ve never made it public. As far as the actual cable ratings we get, views within the first 24 hours and when it airs live are the most important. Does that make sense? It barely makes sense to me so probably not but hopefully you get what I’m saying lol.
